    <stitle>Electrical System Troubleshooting Guide - 3300 Model - LIGHT SYSTEMS - red and amber pupil warning lights
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="x08298194">
        <title>red and amber pupil warning lights</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
            <title>CIRCUIT FUNCTIONS</title>
            <figure id="f082981139" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/G082981109.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"/>
                <caption>Red And Amber Pupil Warning Lights Function Diagram</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. RED AND AMBER PUPIL WARNING LIGHTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. ELECTRICAL SYSTEM CONTROLLER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. RED/AMBER LIGHT FLASHER SWITCH</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>The stop arm and
                <hotlnk xrefid="f082981139">Red &#38; Amber Pupil Warning Lights</hotlnk>
                are activated when the red/amber flasher switch is activated. The steering wheel switches will send a
                message to the ESC to command the lights on. The ESC supplies battery voltage for the red/amber lights.
                The ESC supplies a ground for the stop arm relay to activate.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
